<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/our_system> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "our system" ;
    skos:definition "A system that uses the NLTK PerceptronTagger to add word and part-of-speech pairs as features, lemmatizes tokens using NLTK WordNetLemmatizer, and utilizes four sentiment lexicons." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/S16-1018> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "In our system, we used the NLTK PerceprtronTag- ger2 to add concatenated {word, part-of-speech} pairs as features." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/random_forest> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "random forest" ;
    skos:definition "A random forest is a model trained on 5000 best features selected by the F value of ANOVA, which improved micro-averaged F1 and training time." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/S16-1018> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "Hence, we trained them on 5000 best features selected by the F value of ANOVA which improved micro-averaged F1 and also had a positive influence on training time." ;
    scinex:trainedOn <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/5000_best_features_selected_by_the_f_value_of_anova>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/training_set> .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/random_forests> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "random forests" ;
    skos:definition "Random Forests is a model combined with Support Vector Machines and Gradient Boosting Trees, trained on lexical and semantic features." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/S16-1018> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "The proposed approach combines Ran- dom Forests, Support Vector Machines, and Gradi- ent Boosting Trees, trained on a wide range of lex- ical and semantic features including: n-grams, k- grams, Brown clustering, sentiment lexicons, Senti- WordNet, and part of speech tagged 1-grams." ;
    scinex:trainedOn <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/lexical_and_semantic_features> .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/sentiwordnet> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchArtifact ;
    rdfs:label "sentiwordnet" ;
    skos:definition "A sentiment lexicon used in the system alongside the NRC emotion lexicon, the Hu and Liu Opinion lexicon, and the Multi-perspective Question Answering corpus." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/S16-1018> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "We used this procedure for four sentiment lexicons : the NRC emotion lexicon, Hu and Liu Opinion lexicon, the Multi -perspective Question Answering corpus, and SentiWordNet." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/S16-1018/support_vector_machines> a owl:NamedIndividual,
