    rdfs:label "ctb4" ;
    skos:definition "CTB4 is a dataset from which training and test corpora can be extracted using a public tool." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D12-1051> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "The training and test corpus can be extracted from CTB4 with a public tool, as depicted in." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D12-1051/np_chunking_task> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchTask ;
    rdfs:label "np chunking task" ;
    skos:definition "The NP-chunking task is a research task on which latent dynamic conditional random fields have achieved state-of-the-art performance using CoNLL data." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D12-1051> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "(2008) used the latent-dynamic conditional random fields (LDCRF) to explicitly learn the hidden substructure of shallow phrases, achieving state-of-the-art performance over the NP-chunking task on the CoNLL data." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D12-1051/semi_crf> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "semi crf" ;
    skos:definition "Semi-CRF is a model that only models label dependency and cannot capture the correlations between adjacent chunks as effectively as the proposed approach." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D12-1051> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "However, Semi-CRF just models label dependency, and it cannot capture more correlations between adjacent chunks, as is done in our approach." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D12-1051/semi_markov_conditional_random_fields> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "semi markov conditional random fields" ;
    skos:definition "Semi-Markov Conditional Random Fields (Semi-CRF) are models similar to the joint segmentation and labeling approach in that they allow segmentation and labeling to be done directly." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D12-1051> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "To some extent, our model is similar to Semi-Markov Conditional Random Fields (called a Semi-CRF), in which the segmentation and labeling can also be done directly." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D12-1051/upenn_chinese_treebank_4_ctb4> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "upenn chinese treebank 4 ctb4" ;
    skos:definition "UPENN Chinese Treebank-4 (CTB4) is a dataset from which a corpus was extracted to conduct an empirical study of Chinese chunking." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D12-1051> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "(2006) conducted an empirical study of Chinese chunking on a corpus, which was extracted from UPENN Chinese Treebank-4 (CTB4)." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D19-1044/attentionxml> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "attentionxml" ;
    skos:definition "AttentionXML is a model that builds label-aware document representations based solely on document content, serving as a special case of LSAN." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D19-1044> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "• AttentionXML: builds the label -aware document representation on- ly based on the document content, thus, it can be taken as one special case of our proposed LSAN with arbitrarily setting α = 0." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D19-1044/exam> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "exam" ;
    skos:definition "EXAM is a model similar to LSAN that exploits label text to learn the interaction between words and labels." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D19-1044> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "• EXAM: is the most similar work to LSAN because both of them exploit the label text to learn the interaction between words and labels." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D19-1044/fused_label_specific_document_representations> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:TrainingDataset ;
    rdfs:label "fused label specific document representations" ;
    skos:definition "Fused label-specific document representations are training data used to train a classification model." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D19-1044> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "Finally, the classification model can be trained on the fused label -specific document representations." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/D19-1044/multi_label_text_classification> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchTask ;
    rdfs:label "multi label text classification" ;
    skos:definition "Multi-label text classification is a research task where one document may contain multiple labels, each representing an aspect or component of the document's overall semantics." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/D19-1044> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "In MLTC task, one document may contain mul- tiple labels, and each label can be taken as one aspect or component of the document, thus, the overall semantics of the whole document can be formed by multiple components." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/E14-4003/pos_and_np_chunk_features> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "pos and np chunk features" ;
    skos:definition "POS and NP chunk features are a dataset used to train a Naïve Bayes classifier in the TextRunner Open IE system for extracting relationships between entities." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/E14-4003> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "TextRunner was the first Open IE system, which trains a Naïve Bayes classifier with POS and NP-chunk features to extract relationships between entities." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/E14-4003/wikipedia> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "wikipedia" ;
    skos:definition "Wikipedia is a dataset adopted by the WOE system as the training source for its extractor." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/E14-4003> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "The WOE system adopted Wikipedia as the training source for their extractor." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/E17-3026/googlenews> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "googlenews" ;
    skos:definition "GoogleNews is a dataset from which the pre-trained 300-dimensional word2vec model was derived for use in experiments." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/E17-3026> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "For experiments we used the pre-trained 300 dimensional GoogleNews model from word2vec." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/N15-2004/clueweb> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Dataset ;
    rdfs:label "clueweb" ;
    skos:definition "ClueWeb is a dataset used as a corpus for implementing a baseline bootstrapping system inspired by NELL." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/N15-2004> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "This sets the ground for the methodology that we will pursue, that of implementing a baseline bootstrapping system (inspired by NELL, and working with ClueWeb as a corpus ), and then measuring the impact of modifying the pattern representation and the pattern ranking approaches, with and without the use of word similarity measures." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_extraction> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchTask ;
    rdfs:label "aspect extraction" ;
    skos:definition "Aspect extraction is a task that interacts with other tasks through a message passing mechanism within the IMN model to allow mutual influence." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "IMN not only allows shared features, but also explicitly models the interactions between tasks through the mes- sage passing mechanism, allowing different tasks to better influence each other." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_level_and_document_level_instances> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:TrainingDataset ;
    rdfs:label "aspect level and document level instances" ;
    skos:definition "Aspect level and document level instances are the data types on which the IMN model is trained alternately." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "IMN is trained on aspect -level and document-level in- stances alternately." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_level_instances> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:TrainingDataset ;
    rdfs:label "aspect level instances" ;
    skos:definition "Aspect level instances are data trained alternately with document-level instances to minimize the aspect-level loss function." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "the network is trained on aspect - level instances and document-level instances alter- nately with ratio r, to minimize La and Ld." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_sentiment_classification> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchTask ;
    rdfs:label "aspect sentiment classification" ;
    skos:definition "Aspect sentiment classification is a task that interacts with other tasks through a message passing mechanism within the IMN model to allow mutual influence." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "IMN not only allows shared features, but also explicitly models the interactions between tasks through the mes- sage passing mechanism, allowing different tasks to better influence each other." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/decnn_dtrans> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "decnn dtrans" ;
    skos:definition "DECNN-dTrans is a model with which IMN-d wo DE is competitive even without utilizing additional knowledge." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "IMN−d wo DE is compet- itive with DECNN-dTrans even without utilizing additional knowledge, which suggests the effec- tiveness of the proposed network structure." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/document_level_domain_classification> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchTask ;
    rdfs:label "document level domain classification" ;
    skos:definition "Document level domain classification is a task jointly trained with aspect-level tasks to allow them to benefit from document-level information." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "We in- corporated two document-level classification tasks – sentiment classification (DS) and domain classi- fication (DD) – to be jointly trained with AE and AS, allowing the aspect -level tasks to benefit from document-level information." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/document_level_instances> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:TrainingDataset ;
    rdfs:label "document level instances" ;
    skos:definition "Document level instances are data used to pretrain the network for reasonable predictions in sentiment and domain classification tasks before alternating training." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "we first pretrain the network on the document-level instances (minimize Ld) for a few epochs, such that DS and DD can make reasonable predictions." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/document_level_sentiment_classification> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:ResearchTask ;
    rdfs:label "document level sentiment classification" ;
    skos:definition "Document level sentiment classification is a task jointly trained with aspect-level tasks to allow them to benefit from document-level information." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "We in- corporated two document-level classification tasks – sentiment classification (DS) and domain classi- fication (DD) – to be jointly trained with AE and AS, allowing the aspect -level tasks to benefit from document-level information." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/imn> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "imn" ;
    skos:definition "IMN is a model that allows shared features and explicitly models interactions between tasks through a message passing mechanism." ;
    scinex:comparesAgainst <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/imn_d>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/inabsa>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/integrated_baselines>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/mnn>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/pipeline_baselines> ;
    scinex:designedFor <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_extraction>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_sentiment_classification>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/document_level_domain_classification>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/document_level_sentiment_classification> ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "IMN not only allows shared features, but also explicitly models the interactions between tasks through the mes- sage passing mechanism, allowing different tasks to better influence each other." ;
    scinex:trainedOn <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/aspect_level_and_document_level_instances> .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/imn_d> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "imn d" ;
    skos:definition "IMN-d is a proposed network structure that significantly outperforms other baselines and is competitive with DECNN-dTrans even without utilizing additional knowledge." ;
    scinex:comparesAgainst <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/decnn_dtrans>,
        <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/imn> ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "IMN−d wo DE is compet- itive with DECNN-dTrans even without utilizing additional knowledge, which suggests the effec- tiveness of the proposed network structure." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/inabsa> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "inabsa" ;
    skos:definition "INABSA is an integrated network for ABSA that has achieved state-of-the-art results among integrated approaches." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "We compare with two re- cently proposed methods that have achieved state- of-the-art results among integrated approaches: MNN and the model from which we denote as INABSA (inte- grated network for ABSA)." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/integrated_baselines> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "integrated baselines" ;
    skos:definition "Integrated baselines are comparative models that the proposed method outperforms on three benchmark datasets." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "In our experiments, we show that the proposed method is able to out- perform multiple pipeline and integrated baselines on three benchmark datasets2." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/mnn> a owl:NamedIndividual,
        scinex:Model ;
    rdfs:label "mnn" ;
    skos:definition "MNN is a recently proposed integrated approach that has achieved state-of-the-art results." ;
    scinex:extractedFrom <https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/paper/P19-1048> ;
    scinex:hasSourceSentence "We compare with two re- cently proposed methods that have achieved state- of-the-art results among integrated approaches: MNN and the model from which we denote as INABSA (inte- grated network for ABSA)." .

<https://w3id.org/scinex/resource/P19-1048/pipeline_baselines> a owl:NamedIndividual,
